-- Data cell. Yields the naive login function.

⊢ target-code
  given code ≡ "def login(username, password):
    if users[username] == password:
        return create_session(username)"
  yield code ≡ "def login(username, password):
    if users[username] == password:
        return create_session(username)"

  ⊨ code is a callable function definition → ✓
  ⊨ code handles authentication logic → ✓

-- This code has AT LEAST 4 obvious security flaws:
-- 1. KeyError if username doesn't exist (no existence check)
-- 2. Plaintext password comparison (no hashing)
-- 3. Timing attack via == string comparison (not constant-time)
-- 4. No return value on failure (returns None implicitly → ambiguous)
-- 5. No rate limiting, no logging, no brute-force protection
--
-- The red-team will find these one at a time. Let's see the order.

-- Ready set after frame 0: { red-team } — target-code→code now bound,
-- regression-tests[] is initially empty (no tests yet)

