⊢ harden
  given red-team→vulnerability ≡ "Timing side-channel for username enumeration..."
  given red-team→exploit ≡ "Attacker measures response time..."
  given red-team→category ≡ "info-leak"
  given target-code→code ≡ "import bcrypt
def login(username, password):
    stored_hash = users.get(username)
    if stored_hash is not None and bcrypt.checkpw(password.encode('utf-8'), stored_hash):
        return create_session(username)
    return None"
  given regression-tests ≡ [regression-test-1, regression-test-2]
  yield patched-code, patch-description

  ∴ Fix the timing side-channel. Must not break existing regression tests.

-- LLM evaluation:
-- Fix: ALWAYS run bcrypt.checkpw, even when the user doesn't exist.
-- Use a dummy hash for nonexistent users so the timing is constant.
-- The dummy comparison will always fail, but it takes the same time.

  yield patched-code ≡ "import bcrypt

DUMMY_HASH = bcrypt.hashpw(b'dummy', bcrypt.gensalt())

def login(username, password):
    stored_hash = users.get(username, DUMMY_HASH)
    if bcrypt.checkpw(password.encode('utf-8'), stored_hash):
        if username in users:
            return create_session(username)
    return None"

  yield patch-description ≡ "Added DUMMY_HASH constant. When username not found, users.get() returns DUMMY_HASH instead of None. bcrypt.checkpw always runs (~100ms for both cases). Even if checkpw accidentally matches the dummy, the explicit 'username in users' check prevents session creation. Timing is now constant regardless of username existence."

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ patched-code is valid Python → ✓
--   ⊨ patched-code fixes timing side-channel → ✓ (always runs bcrypt)
--   ⊨ preserves correct login behavior → ✓ (valid creds still work, invalid still fail)

-- SUBTLE BUG CHECK: what if password happens to match the dummy hash?
-- bcrypt.checkpw(user_password, DUMMY_HASH) could theoretically return True
-- if the user typed "dummy". But the `if username in users` check catches
-- this — nonexistent user can't create a session even if hash matches.
-- Double-gated: hash match AND user exists. Correct.

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- frame 11: verify-patch (iteration 3)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

