-- LLM evaluation:
-- The code is getting harder to attack. Let me think deeper.
--
-- No rate limiting. An attacker can call login() in a tight loop — millions
-- of attempts per second (limited only by bcrypt's ~100ms per call, so ~10/sec
-- per thread, but parallelizable across threads). No lockout. No delay. No
-- logging. Classic brute-force vulnerability.
--
-- With bcrypt at work factor 12, each attempt takes ~100ms. For a 6-char
-- lowercase password: 26^6 = 308M combinations. At 10 attempts/sec/thread
